urls.title: rang: make ancient R code run again
urls.description: Reproducibility is a big issue in the (computational) world of science. Code that runs today might not run tomorrow because packages are updated, functions deprecated or removed, and whole programming languages change. In the case of R, there exist a great variety of packages to ensure that code written today, also runs tomorrow (and hopefully also in a few years). Ths includes packages such as renv, groundhog, miniCRAN, and Require.

tweets.text:
